DUNBARTONSHIRE Disability Sport Club is launching a pilot swimming project at the Play Drome Leisure Centre in Clydebank on Sunday.Children and young people affected by disability and their families are invited to attend the event to show their support.The aim is to set up a permanent swimming club catering for the needs of local children and young people affected by disability.Club Chairperson, Allan Clark stated &quot;This is a great opportunity for our club to answer the needs of the community. The club committee has been working tirelessly for the last ten months to make DDSC SWIM a reality. I would like to take this opportunity on the behalf of the Dunbartonshire Disability Sports Club to thank West Dunbartonshire Council, West Dunbartonshire Leisure Trust and the Leisure Trust's Swimming Development Officer, Lorna Smith for their continuing support.&quot;